Cleaning¶

  • Null values in BorrowerAPR, ProsperRating, ProsperScore, EmploymentStatus, CreditScoreRangeLower, CreditScoreRangeUpper, CurrentCreditLines, OpenCreditLines, InquiriesLast6Months, TotalInquiries, CurrentDelinquencies, AmountDelinquent, RevolvingCreditBalance, BankcardUtilization, TotalTrades, TradesOpenedLast6Months, DebtToIncomeRatio, TotalProsperLoans and ClosedDate.
  • ListingCreationDate, ClosedDate and LoanOriginationDate is in string format.
  • ListingCategory is in number but it should be in string.

Null values cleaning¶

  • Filling the null value because few columns have some default value if no value available.
    • CurrentCreditLines, OpenCreditLines, InquiriesLast6Months, TotalInquiries, CurrentDelinquencies, AmountDelinquent, RevolvingCreditBalance, BankcardUtilization, TotalTrades, TradesOpenedLast6Months and TotalProsperLoans.

In [11]:
def change_list(x):
    ListingCategory = {0 : 'Not Available', 1 : 'Debt Consolidation', 2 : 'Home Loan', 3 : 'Business',
                       4 : 'Personal Loan', 5 : 'Student Use', 6 : 'Auto', 7 : 'Personal Loan',
                       8 : 'Personal Loan', 9 : 'Auto', 10 : 'Personal Loan', 11 : 'Wedding Loans',
                       12 : 'Green Loans', 13 : 'Home Loan', 14 : 'Personal Loan', 15 : 'Medical or Dental',
                       16 : 'Auto', 17 : 'Auto', 18 : 'Taxes',
                       19 : 'Vacation', 20 : 'Wedding Loans'}
    return ListingCategory[int(x)]

data['ListingCategory'] = data['ListingCategory'].apply(change_list)
  • Change the LoanOriginationDate and Closed date to datetime format from string.
In [12]:
data.LoanOriginationDate = pd.to_datetime(data.LoanOriginationDate)
data.ClosedDate= pd.to_datetime(data.ClosedDate)
